      • testSchemaChangeOnNonUnnestColumn_InMultilevelCase

        public void testSchemaChangeOnNonUnnestColumn_InMultilevelCase()
                                                        throws Exception
        This test is different than testSchemaChangeOnNonUnnestColumn() because with multilevel when the first Lateral see's a schema change it creates a new batch with new vector references. Hence the second lateral will receive a new incoming with new vector references with OK_NEW_SCHEMA outcome. Now even though there is schema change for non-unnest column the second Unnest has to again setup it's transfer pairs since vector reference for unnest field has changed for second Unnest. Whereas in other test since there is only 1 Lateral followed by Scan, the incoming for lateral which has schema change will be handled by Scan in such a way that it only updates vector of affected column. Hence in this case vector corresponding to unnest field will not be affected and it will work fine.
        Throws:
        Exception
